About this item

  • Simple Installation: As a dimmer compatible with Single-Pole, 4 Way, and 3 Way Smart Dimmer Switches, the PDF installation guide will teach you basic circuit knowledge, installation methods, and basic device operation.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      3.0 out of 5 stars The lighting on this is a deal killer
      Reviewed in the United States on April 19, 2021
      Verified Purchase
      Functionally, the 3 gang, single pole switches do the job. Nothing to really complain about there. My grief is with the physical lights on the switches themselves. Each switch has a fairly bright, small LED light that switches between red and green depending on whether the associated device is on or off. While I appreciate being able to tell whether a device is on or off by looking at the switch, it is intuitive. Does red mean off? Does green mean on? I'm sure eventually, it would become more natural, but I don't know why you need different colors instead of on or off. I switched to a different brand that has a very dim light that shows when the device is off, and no light when the device is on. That is both intuitive, and helpful, without being distracting in the dark.
